&gt; It looks like you are having trouble getting the boost libraries
&gt; linked in.
&gt; 
&gt; The problem is that the boost library has this complex naming
&gt; convention for its libraries and it is hard to write a script that can
&gt; handle every possible case.  I believe that the creators of cmake are
&gt; working on a script which is comprehensive enough to work on all systems.
&gt; 
&gt; In the meantime, here is what you can do:
&gt; 
&gt; 1) Get the boost library (either by building yourself or using a binary)
&gt; 
&gt; 2) Find out what library name the boost threading examples use.
&gt; 
&gt; 3) edit the CMakelists.txt inside the Hypercube_NEAT directory and in
&gt; the TARGET_LINK_LIBRARIES(...) section, replace the boost thread
&gt; library name with the appropriate name.
